# Feature 029: Complete User Guide Documentation with Screenshots

## Overview
Transform the existing technical API documentation into a comprehensive, user-friendly guide with step-by-step instructions and screenshots for all 17 major system features. This will significantly improve user onboarding, reduce support requests, and provide self-service learning resources.

## Clarifications

### Session 2025-10-19
- Q: When should screenshots be automatically regenerated after UI changes? → A: Never (screenshots are static artifacts)

## Problem Statement
The current Documentation section (`client/src/components/dashboard/documentation.tsx`) focuses primarily on technical API reference material, which is useful for developers but not accessible for end users. Users need:

1. **Visual guidance** - Screenshots showing what they should see at each step
2. **Step-by-step instructions** - Clear, numbered steps for common tasks
3. **Feature-specific guides** - Dedicated guides for each major feature
4. **Troubleshooting help** - Common issues and solutions
5. **Quick reference** - Fast access to frequently used workflows

## Business Value
- **Reduce onboarding time** from days to hours for new users
- **Decrease support tickets** by 40-60% through self-service documentation
- **Improve user adoption** of advanced features (widgets, analytics, ordering)
- **Professional appearance** enhances system credibility and value
- **Training resource** reduces training costs and time

## Scope

### In Scope
1. **User Guide Section** - New "User Guides" navigation item in Documentation
2. **17 Feature Guides** - Complete guides for all sidebar features:
   - Dashboard
   - Widget Dashboards
   - Widget Builder
   - Widget Templates
   - Stock Control
   - Stock Ordering
   - Sales Analytics
   - Case Size Management
   - Stock Profiles
   - Supplier Profiles
   - Sales Aggregation
   - Waste Management
   - Expiry Management
   - Tasks & Handover
   - Reports
   - Data Upload
   - Settings

3. **Screenshot Automation** - Playwright script to capture 50+ screenshots
4. **Responsive Design** - Mobile-friendly documentation viewer
5. **Search & Navigation** - Easy access to specific guides

### Out of Scope
- Video tutorials (future enhancement)
- Interactive demos (future enhancement)
- Multi-language support (future enhancement)
- PDF export (future enhancement)
- Printable versions (future enhancement)
- Automatic screenshot regeneration on UI changes (screenshots are static artifacts managed manually)

## User Stories

### User Story 1: New User Onboarding
**As a** new system user
**I want** visual step-by-step guides for each feature
**So that** I can learn the system independently without extensive training

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Can access User Guides from Documentation sidebar
- [ ] Each feature has a dedicated guide with screenshots
- [ ] Step-by-step instructions are numbered and clear
- [ ] Screenshots show actual system UI with annotations
- [ ] Mobile-responsive layout works on tablets

**Priority:** High

### User Story 2: Quick Reference for Common Tasks
**As an** existing user
**I want** quick reference guides for common workflows
**So that** I can refresh my memory without searching through documentation

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] "Common Tasks" section for each feature
- [ ] Quick links to frequently used workflows
- [ ] Keyboard shortcuts documented (where applicable)
- [ ] Search functionality to find specific tasks
- [ ] Bookmarkable URLs for specific guides

**Priority:** Medium

### User Story 3: Troubleshooting Self-Service
**As a** user encountering an issue
**I want** troubleshooting guides with screenshots
**So that** I can resolve problems without contacting support

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] "Troubleshooting" section for each feature
- [ ] Common error messages explained
- [ ] Solution steps with screenshots
- [ ] Links to related guides
- [ ] Contact support option if unresolved

**Priority:** Medium

### User Story 4: Feature Discovery
**As a** user looking to improve my workflow
**I want** to browse available features with visual examples
**So that** I can discover and adopt features I wasn't aware of

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Overview page showing all 17 features
- [ ] Feature cards with preview screenshots
- [ ] "What you can do" descriptions
- [ ] Difficulty indicators (Beginner/Intermediate/Advanced)
- [ ] Related features linked together

**Priority:** Low

## Technical Requirements

### Frontend Components

#### 1. Documentation Structure Enhancement
**File:** `client/src/components/dashboard/documentation.tsx`

**Changes:**
- Add "User Guides" to sections array
- Create `renderUserGuides()` function
- Add tabbed interface for feature selection
- Integrate screenshot viewer component

#### 2. Reusable Components (NEW)
**Files to Create:**

**`client/src/components/dashboard/UserGuideSection.tsx`**
```typescript
interface GuideStep {
  title: string;
  description: string;
  screenshot: string;
  tips?: string[];
  warnings?: string[];
}

interface UserGuideSectionProps {
  featureName: string;
  overview: string;
  gettingStarted: string[];
  steps: GuideStep[];
  commonTasks?: GuideStep[];
  troubleshooting?: { issue: string; solution: string; }[];
}
```

**`client/src/components/dashboard/ScreenshotViewer.tsx`**
```typescript
interface ScreenshotViewerProps {
  src: string;
  alt: string;
  caption?: string;
  annotations?: Annotation[];
  zoomable?: boolean;
}
```

### Screenshot Automation

#### Playwright Script
**File:** `scripts/capture-user-guide-screenshots.ts`

**Requirements:**
- Headless: false (for visual confirmation)
- Viewport: 1920x1080 (desktop), 768x1024 (tablet)
- Format: PNG with compression
- Naming: `{feature}-{step}-{description}.png`
- Annotations: Optional overlay markup

**Screenshot Categories:**

1. **Navigation Screenshots** (17 total)
   - Each feature's sidebar navigation
   - Active state indication
   - Mobile menu state

2. **Feature Overview Screenshots** (17 total)
   - Initial landing page for each feature
   - Key UI elements highlighted
   - Empty state vs populated state

3. **Workflow Screenshots** (100+ total)
   - Step-by-step task completion
   - Form interactions
   - Success confirmations
   - Error states

4. **Detail Screenshots** (50+ total)
   - Specific UI components
   - Filter panels
   - Modal dialogs
   - Tooltips and help text

### Screenshot Organization
```
public/
