## Success Metrics

### Quantitative
- **Screenshot Coverage:** 50+ screenshots across all features
- **Feature Coverage:** All 17 features documented
- **Page Load Performance:** <2s for guide pages
- **Mobile Compatibility:** 100% responsive on tablets
- **Screenshot Quality:** Min 1920x1080 resolution

### Qualitative
- **User Feedback:** 90%+ satisfaction rating
- **Completeness:** Users can complete tasks independently
- **Clarity:** Steps are clear without additional explanation
- **Professionalism:** Documentation appears polished and complete

## Non-Functional Requirements

### Performance
- Documentation page loads in <2 seconds
- Screenshots lazy-load below the fold
- Images compressed to <500KB each
- Total page size <10MB

### Accessibility
- Alt text for all screenshots
- Keyboard navigation support
- Screen reader friendly structure
- High contrast text on images

### Maintainability
- Screenshot naming convention documented
- Manual update process defined (Playwright script re-run when needed)
- Screenshots version controlled in Git
- Automated screenshot refresh capability available via Playwright script (manual trigger only)

## Dependencies
- Playwright (already installed)
- Current documentation.tsx structure
- Existing UI components (Card, Tabs, Badge, etc.)
- Public directory for static assets

## Risks & Mitigation

### Risk 1: Screenshot Maintenance Burden
**Impact:** High
**Mitigation:**
- Automated screenshot capture script (manual trigger)
- Maintain script for easy re-capture when UI changes
- Screenshots are static artifacts - no automatic regeneration
- Document manual update process

### Risk 2: Content Creation Time
**Impact:** Medium
**Mitigation:**
- Phased approach (priority features first)
- Reusable content templates
- Focus on most-used features initially
- Can add features incrementally

### Risk 3: UI Changes Breaking Screenshots
**Impact:** Medium
**Mitigation:**
- Playwright script can quickly re-capture (manual process)
- Screenshots tracked in Git version control
- Annotate screenshots to remain relevant longer
- Manual updates triggered only when UI changes materially affect documentation

